    "body": "@sipa The block filter headers commit the the filter header of the previous block and BIP 157 defines a filter header for the genesis block, which is the motivation for this PR. The BIP could be amended to define the filter header of the genesis as 0, but I feel like this is a silly reason to change the BIP. Also, the genesis block is a block -- it's very unintuitive to me that it would get skipped by default just because it's a special block with no effect on the chain state.",
